title: ULA rolls Atlas 5 rocket to launch pad at Cape Canaveral
summary: United Launch Alliance teams at Cape Canaveral rolled an Atlas 5 rocket to its launch pad Wednesday, moving the launcher into position for liftoff Thursday evening with a pair of geostationary satellites for the U.S. Space Force.

title: Falcon 9 set to launch SES-22 geostationary communications satellite
summary: SpaceX is scheduled to launch the SES-22 communications satellite to geostationary transfer orbit on the 27th Falcon 9 launch of 2022. The launch is scheduled for Wednesday, June 29, at 5:04 PM EDT (21:04 UTC). This is the beginning of a two-hour and 10-minute launch window from Launch Complex 40 at the Cape Canaveral Space Force Station.

title: Avio gets pandemic recovery funds to develop launchers for the 2030s
summary: Italian rocket maker Avio secured 340 million euros ($358 million) in government funding June 29 to develop launch vehicles for the next decade.
